## Phase 2 — the shaping fact
The current pipeline **never produces a local video file** — publishing is
100% Playwright (creates a Twitch clip in-browser, clicks "Send Draft to
TikTok"; `filePath` is always `null`). YouTube's Content API has **no
share-UI shortcut — it needs actual video bytes uploaded.** So Phase 2 must
ADD local video production that doesn't exist today:
- **Raw VOD → YouTube:** yt-dlp full VOD download → upload. No rendering.
- **Shorts → YouTube:** `downloadVodSegment` (exists) → render 9:16 (resurrect
  the currently-dead `src/processing/ffmpegPipeline.js`) → caption → upload.

